---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import GitHubLogo from "../components/GitHubLogo.astro";
import PageHeader from "../components/PageHeader.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="CapitalBench Audit And Data Docs"
  description="CapitalBench audit and data pages for scoring, fairness, limits, asset lists, and round source files."
>
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="Audit"
    title="Audit And Data"
    summary="Check how the tests work, how scores are calculated, and where the source files live."
  />
  <section class="section compact">
    <div class="resolution-callout">
      <div>
        <span class="panel-kicker">Start here</span>
        <h2>How To Read CapitalBench</h2>
        <p>
          Start with how it works, then scoring. Open a test round when you want the prompt, model portfolios, prices,
          and audit hashes.
        </p>
      </div>
      <a class="action-link action-primary" href="/rounds">Open test rounds</a>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="grid-3">
      <article class="feature">
        <h3><a href="/methodology">How It Works</a></h3>
        <p>The simple process: same information, saved portfolios, real market scores.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="feature">
        <h3><a href="/scoring">Scoring</a></h3>
        <p>How returns, S&amp;P context, and CapitalBench Score are calculated.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="feature">
        <h3><a href="/fairness">Fairness</a></h3>
        <p>Why models get the same information and why old scores are not rewritten.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="feature">
        <h3><a href="/limitations">Limitations</a></h3>
        <p>Noise, sample size, hosted model changes, and non-advice boundaries.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="feature">
        <h3><a href="/insights">Insights</a></h3>
        <p>Readable signals generated from model positioning, benchmark results, risk appetite, and scoring windows.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="feature">
        <h3><a href="/models/patterns">Model Behavior Patterns</a></h3>
        <p>Side-by-side model behavior profiles covering risk appetite, concentration, turnover, peer overlap, and sample caveats.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="feature">
        <h3>
          <a
            href="https://github.com/ishtiaqrahman/capitalbench/blob/main/docs/insights_engine_plan.md"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer"
          >
            Insights Engine Plan
          </a>
        </h3>
        <p>Research and implementation plan for deterministic and LLM-assisted benchmark insights.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="feature">
        <h3><a href="/universe">Asset List</a></h3>
        <p>The public asset choices available to models in each test.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="feature">
        <h3><a href="/rounds/CB-2026-05-10-1M">Round 1</a></h3>
        <p>Model portfolios, starting prices, status, and audit hashes.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="feature">
        <h3><a href="/changelog">Changelog</a></h3>
        <p>Major public changes to the benchmark, site, methodology, data, and operations.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="feature">
        <h3>
          <a
            class="repository-link"
            href="https://github.com/ishtiaqrahman/capitalbench"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer"
            data-analytics-event="github_repository_click"
            data-analytics-param-location="docs_card"
          >
            <GitHubLogo size={17} />
            Repository
          </a>
        </h3>
        <p>Source code, schemas, local files, and implementation history.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
